Maintainer: Ben Wiseman <benjamin.h.wiseman@gmail.com>
Description: This package uses Google's Universal Sentence Encoder, simplifies all the guff, and turns it into a sentiment analysis package.
    Benefits:
        1) Tolerates spelling mistakes
        2) Not dependent on exactly matching a fixed dictionary
        3) Requires less pre-processing
        4) More powerful than dictionary-based methods
    Drawback:
        1) Requires a lot or RAM and, without a GPU install, can be a tad slow on larger datasets
    Effectivelly, if you have a reasonably powerful computer, you can use sentiment.ai as a more flexible, powerful, and modern approach to sentiment analysis. 
